The paper discusses a method for keyword search against structured databases, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information retrieval (cs.IR) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the use of standard IR techniques, such as ranking, which further supports the classification of the paper under cs.IR. Additionally, the paper discusses the representation of the database as a collection of independent units, which could potentially involve natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Finally, the paper mentions a prototype implementation, which could involve deep learning (cs.DL) techniques for building the system.
